      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;specification&#34;&gt;specification&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-this-is&#34;&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;Specification&lt;/strong&gt; is a &lt;a href=&#34;../resource.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;Resource&lt;/a&gt; that describes one thing — a mathematical object, a system behavior, a convention, or a unit type — by stating what is true of it, what is forbidden, and what is open.&#xA;Every normative claim uses RFC 2119 keywords.&#xA;A Specification MUST NOT invent claims that are not settled; unsettled claims go in Open questions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;required-sections&#34;&gt;Required sections&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Every Specification MUST contain the following sections, in this order:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
